FBIS3-25195 "drafr028_c_94005" FBIS-AFR-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Comments on KwaZulu Demands MB0902133694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1100 GMT 9 Feb 94 MB0902133694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Constitutional Development Minister Roelf Meyer says recent demands made by King Goodwill Zwelithini of the Zulus are tantamount to a call for independence. Mr. Meyer told the SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] that the king's delegation had made specific demands about the future of the kwaZulu kingdom during talks with President F.W. de Klerk. He would not divulge the details but said it was a cause for concern as the matter could redirect the future of the negotiations.
